source "https://github.com/Tieske/CopasTimer.git"
summary "Copas add-on to provide timers, background tasks and optionally events"
detail "Copas Timer is a module that adds a timer capability to the"
detail "Copas scheduler. It provides the same base functions step and"
detail "loop as Copas (it actually replaces them) except that it will"
detail "also check for (and run) timers expiring and run background"
detail "workers if there is no IO or timer to handle. It also adds"
detail "methods to allow for a controlled exit from the loop."
detail "As an optional component an 'eventer' is available to dispatch"
detail "events as background tasks in Copas Timer."
license "MIT/X11"
homepage "http://www.thijsschreijer.nl/blog/?page_id=537"
depend "copas"
import "copas.timer" "source/copas/timer.lua"
import "copas.eventer" "source/copas/eventer.lua"
